title: Golden Retriever puppy rescued after being abandoned | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad Golden Retriever puppy Jake is found alive after being abandoned in an Oregon apartment for a MONTH by his owner who went home to China A Golden Retriever puppy was found alive after being left alone in an apartment by his owner, a University of Oregon college student The four-month-old puppy, named Jake, weighed ten pounds and was probably left for a month He spent time at an emergency veterinary hospital then was put in foster care Molly Monette, who is the Eugene Police Department's Animal Welfare Supervisor, was Jake's foster parent and adopted him Published: 04:41 GMT, 11 February 2017 | Updated: 07:18 GMT, 11 February 2017 92 shares
